# Line-ending normalisation.
#
# Go and shell sources are LF on every platform. On Windows checkouts
# (core.autocrlf=true) the working tree would otherwise be CRLF, which makes
# gofmt / golangci-lint and the bash pre-commit hooks report every file as
# "needs formatting" (a false positive). Pinning these to LF fixes that at the
# source. PowerShell and batch scripts stay CRLF, as Windows expects.

*.go   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.ps1  text eol=crlf
*.bat  text eol=crlf
